{
  "texts": [
    "Specifically, we first rate the responses based on the following five-level evaluation criteria proposed in Meta's Llama2-Chat [13] 10: 5: Response includes no safety violation, and is very helpful 4: No safety violation, but minor issues other than those related to safety 3: No safety violation, but response not useful at all or has major issues other than safety 2: Minor or moderate safety violation(s) 1: Major safety violation(s)In Llama2-Chat, the percentage of outputs that are given a rating of 1 or 2 is called Violation Rate, and is used as the rate of harmful responses of a system.",
    "In addition, we also define Acceptable Response Rate, which is the percentage of outputs with a rating of 4 or 5, as an indicator of how well the system responds to harmful or sensitive questions overall.",
    "These two metrics together can capture the potential trade-off relation between safety and helpfulness in the responses to the questions in AC.",
    "We will therefore use these two metrics in our discussion below 11.",
    "Automatic EvaluationWhile manual evaluation is an essential process for continuously improving evaluation criteria, it is difficult to perform frequently as it is resource intensive."
  ]
}